	(text "- USART1_TX(STM_PG8) -> ESP_RX\n- USART1_RX(STM PF13) -> ESP_TX\n- For power and UART, use the 5V0 and {UART} labels.\n- Take note of whichever UART you connect the ESP to (1, 2, 3, 4)\n- Add anything else you want, ie status LEDs, decoupling capacitor,\n   etc. Arduino shield schematics are good examples\n- Any additional parts should be:\n    - Available on JLCPCB, in stock\n    - Put datasheet in docs/ESP32/ folder\n	- Follow schematic shown in datasheet if possible"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 212.09 26.924 0)
		(effects
